.TH Q 1 "July 2026" "q 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
q \- command line queue and execution tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B q
.RB [ \-l | \-\-list ]
.br
.B q
.RB [ \-k | \-\-kill ]
.I job_id
.br
.B q
.RB [ \-L | \-\-logs ]
.I job_id
.br
.B q
.I command
.RI [ args... ]
.br
.B q
.RB [ \-h | \-\-help ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B q
is a lightweight utility that queues command execution and runs jobs in parallel in the background, managed by a background daemon
.BR qdaemon .
If the daemon is not running when a command is queued or listed, the client starts it automatically.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list
List all jobs currently in the queue, including their ID, status, PID, start time, elapsed duration, and command. This is the default behavior if no arguments are provided.
.TP
.BR \-k ", " \-\-kill " \fIjob_id\fR"
Kill a running job or cancel a queued job.
.TP
.BR \-L ", " \-\-logs " \fIjob_id\fR"
Print the captured standard output (stdout) and standard error (stderr) of the specified job.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a summary of command usage and options.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The daemon reads its configuration from a TOML file. The path is searched in the following order:
.IP 1.
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/q/q.conf
(usually
.IR ~/.config/q/q.conf )
.IP 2.
.I ~/.q/q.conf
.PP
The configuration options are:
.TP
.B max_parallel_jobs
The maximum number of jobs allowed to run concurrently (default is 2).
.TP
.B max_completed_jobs
The maximum number of finished jobs retained in the history/spool directory (default is 50).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.q/
Directory containing daemon runtime state.
.TP
.I ~/.q/q.sock
Unix domain socket used for client-daemon communication.
.TP
.I ~/.q/qdaemon.pid
Process ID of the running daemon.
.TP
.I ~/.q/spool/
Spool directory containing metadata and logs for each job.
